The paper discusses improvements to TCP and MPTCP protocols for better performance in lossy and high delay networks, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also mentions forward error correction (FEC) and its integration with TCP, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper evaluates the performance of the proposed framework for real application traffic, such as video streaming and web services, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM) and distributed computing (cs.DC).
